title: Tom Brady, New England Patriots vs. New York Jets: Start time, what TV channel, how to watch live stream online
text:
Tom Brady and the New England Patriots are used to these kind of challenges. The 2015 Super Bowl champs are unbeaten during the 2015 season and the New York Jets see their game against the Patriots as a chance to make a statement Sunday morning (KOIN-6, (CBS), 10 a.m. PT/1 p.m. ET) .
The Patriots (5-0) look unbeatable. They are averaging a league-leading 36.6 points a game and have won their games by an average margin of 16 points. They have dominated the Jets in recent seasons, winning seven of the last eight games. Quarterback Tom Brady has a 21-7 record as a starter against the Jets during his career.
The Jets (4-1) have usually given the Patriots a tough game. The Jets lost by a combined three points in the two games during the 2014 season. They possess a stifling defense that ranks No. 1 in total defense in the NFL and they have allowed 75 points, fewest in the league.
The Jets offense features a running attack that averages 146 yards a game, tops in the NFL. A time-consuming ground attack could be a key element in the game - keeping Brady and the Patriots offense off the field.
If you want to watch the Jets-Patriots game, here's what you need to know:
What : New York Jets at New England Patriots
Where : Gillette Stadium, Foxborough, MA
When : Sunday, Oct. 25, 10 a.m. PT/1 p.m. ET
TV : KOIN-6 (CBS)
Watch online : You can watch a live stream online on DirecTV's live stream package.
-- Geoffrey C. Arnold | @geoffreyCarnold
